# GPTOPT NIP STARTER FILE
# Preset: Halo Infinite Competitive
# Status: strategy manifest / not yet validated against a real exported NPI .nip sample

[Profile]
Name=GPTOPT - Halo Infinite Competitive
Intent=Support competitive play priorities: consistency, low latency, and repeatable frametime behavior
Scope=Game-specific profile only
Game=Halo Infinite

[Targets]
FrameCapStrategy=Use one deliberate cap path and do not stack multiple limiters blindly
VRRStrategy=Test only with the exact sync path in use
TextureFilteringQuality=High Performance only if distant clarity loss is acceptable
ThreadedOptimization=Auto unless a direct A/B test proves otherwise
ShaderCache=Enabled
PowerManagement=Game-specific maximum performance only if it improves consistency without creating worse idle/global behavior
AnisotropicFiltering=Application-controlled
Antialiasing=Application-controlled
LatencyApproach=Prefer the game's own latency path or sync method first; use profile-level changes as a second step

[Validation]
Check1=Average FPS on the same map and route
Check2=1 percent low on the same route
Check3=Frametime spike frequency
Check4=GPU utilization swing behavior
Check5=Input feel consistency

[Rollback]
Method=Export the original profile first, change one bucket at a time, and keep the route fixed during testing
